:"circa 1435","1464":"1464","1573":"1573","1430":"1430","Drumlanrig Castle, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Drumlanrig Castle, Dumfriesshire, Schotland","Auchingill, , Caithness, Scotland":"Auckingill, Caithness, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Scotland":"Schotland","Galloway, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Dumfriesshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1477–1573":"1477–1573","1430–1484":"1430–1484","1448–1498":"1448–1498","1460–1499":"1460–1499","1464–Female":"1464–Deceased","1470–1550":"1470–1550","1499–Male":"1499–Deceased","1501–1599":"1501–1599","1415–1464":"1415–1464","1410–1482":"1410–1482","1550":"1550","1484":"1484","1482":"1482","1460":"1460","1470":"1470","1415":"1415","1448":"1448","1501":"1501","1599":"1599","1477":"1477","1499":"1499","1410":"1410","1498":"1498","about 1435":"about 1435","1464":"1464","1573":"1573","1430":"1430","Drumlanrig Castle, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Drumlanrig Castle, Dumfriesshire, Scotland","Auchingill, , Caithness, Scotland":"Auckingill, Caithness, Scotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","Galloway, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Dumfriesshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Douglas","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from any of various places called from their situation on a river named with Gaelic <i>dubh</i> ‘dark, black’ + <i>glas</i> ‘stream’ (a derivative of <i>glas</i> ‘blue’). There are several localities in Scotland and Ireland so named, but the one from which the surname is derived in most if not all cases is Douglas in Lanarkshire 20 miles south of Glasgow, the original stronghold of the influential Douglas family and their retainers.","History: The family taking their name from Douglas in Lanarkshire were of Flemish origin. They rose to great prominence in the 14th and 15th centuries, controlling the earldoms of Douglas, Morton, and Angus, and later, Queensberry."],"variants":[{"name":"Douglass","meanings":["Scottish and English (Durham and Northumbria): variant of   Douglas  .","History: William Douglass, a physician recognized for his identification and description of an epidemic of scarlet fever, was born <i>c.</i> 1691 in Gifford, Haddington County, Scotland, and settled in Boston in 1718. The abolitionist, orator, and journalist Frederick Douglass assumed the name after escaping from slavery in 1838 and traveling to Massachusetts. Son of a white father and a slave with some Indian blood, he was born Frederick Augustus Washington Bailey <i>c.</i> 1817 in Tuckahoe, MD."]}]},{"name":"Elspeth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["contracted form of   Elizabeth  , also found outside Scotland."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Elspeth Douglas was born in 1477, in Drumlanrig Castle, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, her father, Sir William Douglas 3rd Baron of Drumlanrig, was 62 and her mother, Margaret Carlyle, was 67. She had at least 2 sons with Robert Maitland. She died in 1573, in Scotland, at the age of 96."},"et":{"1477–1573":"1477–1573","1430–1484":"1430–1484","1448–1498":"1448–1498","1460–1499":"1460–1499","1464–Female":"1464–Surnud","1470–1550":"1470–1550","1499–Male":"1499–Surnud","1501–1599":"1501–1599","1415–1464":"1415–1464","1410–1482":"1410–1482","1550":"1550","1484":"1484","1482":"1482","1460":"1460","1470":"1470","1415":"1415","1448":"1448","1501":"1501","1599":"1599","1477":"1477","1499":"1499","1410":"1410","1498":"1498","about 1435":"umbes 1435","1464":"1464","1573":"1573","1430":"1430","Drumlanrig Castle, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Drumlanrig Castle, Dumfriesshire, Scotland","Auchingill, , Caithness, Scotland":"Auckingill, Caithness, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","Galloway, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Dumfriesshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1477–1573":"1477–1573","1430–1484":"1430–1484","1448–1498":"1448–1498","1460–1499":"1460–1499","